"name given to each output varies from driver to driver. What one driver "
"calls `HDMI-1`, another might call `HDMI1`. So the first step is to run "
"man:xrandr[1] to list all the available outputs:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/handbook/x11/_index.adoc:403
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"% xrandr\n"
"Screen 0: minimum 320 x 200, current 1366 x 768, maximum 8192 x 8192\n"
"LVDS1 connected 1366x768+0+0 (normal left inverted right x axis y axis) "
"344mm x 193mm\n"
"   1366x768      60.04*+\n"
"   1024x768      60.00\n"
"   800x600       60.32    56.25\n"
"   640x480       59.94\n"
